[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":469},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2020\u002F09\u002F27\u002Flearn-hexo-14-hueman-theme\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2020\u002F09\u002F27\u002Flearn-hexo-14-hueman-theme\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2020\u002F09\u002F27\u002Flearn-hexo-14-hueman-theme\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2020\u002F09\u002F27\u002Flearn-hexo-14-hueman-theme\u002F":446,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2020\u002F09\u002F27\u002Flearn-hexo-14-hueman-theme\u002F":455},"\u002Fhexo\u002F20200927\u002F1530073462\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":429,"date":430,"description":19,"extension":431,"lang":386,"meta":432,"navigation":433,"path":434,"readingMinutes":435,"seo":436,"standalone":437,"stem":438,"tags":439,"tldr":443,"updated":430,"url":444,"__hash__":445},"content\u002Fen\u002FHexo\u002Flearn-hexo-14-hueman-theme.md","(14) Learning Hexo from Scratch - Themes: Hueman","2643700351",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":423},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,32,39,46,49,55,58,66,82,110,115,119,126,140,160,182,191,203,208,211,217,224,232,236,242,245,289,302,368,375,381,400,406,413,416,419],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"Now we'll try installing our first theme. There will be more themes after this one — the goal is to get comfortable with the install flow.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"installing-hueman","Installing Hueman",[17,25,26,27,31],{},"Hexo theme installation uses git commands, including ",[28,29,30],"code",{},"git clone",". So at the very least you'll want to have seen this command before, otherwise you'll have a lot of \"wait, what?\" moments.",[17,33,34,35,38],{},"First, open your terminal and ",[28,36,37],{},"cd"," into your Hexo project (or just open VSCode if you're lazy).",[17,40,41],{},[42,43],"img",{"alt":44,"src":45},"Terminal","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FHexo\u002F%E8%A9%A6%E8%91%97%E5%AD%B8%20Hexo%20%E7%B3%BB%E5%88%97\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202020-08-12%2022.02.12.png",[17,47,48],{},"Then click the GitHub Code button on the theme repo and copy the link the arrow points to:",[17,50,51],{},[42,52],{"alt":53,"src":54},"Copy repo link","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FHexo\u002F%E8%A9%A6%E8%91%97%E5%AD%B8%20Hexo%20%E7%B3%BB%E5%88%97\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202020-08-12%2022.04.45.png",[17,56,57],{},"Now in the terminal, run:",[17,59,60,61,65],{},"(",[62,63,64],"del",{},"Knowing you might be lazy, I'll just paste it for you.",")",[67,68,73],"pre",{"className":69,"code":70,"language":71,"meta":72,"style":72},"language-cmd shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","git clone https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Fppoffice\u002Fhexo-theme-hueman.git themes\u002Fhueman\n","cmd","",[28,74,75],{"__ignoreMap":72},[76,77,80],"span",{"class":78,"line":79},"line",1,[76,81,70],{},[17,83,84,85,87,88,94,95,98,99,101,102,105,106,109],{},"I'll skip explaining ",[28,86,30],{},". The URL ",[89,90,91],"a",{"href":91,"rel":92},"https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Fppoffice\u002Fhexo-theme-hueman.git",[93],"nofollow"," is the path we just copied, and the last bit ",[28,96,97],{},"themes\u002Fhueman"," means: clone the project into the ",[28,100,97],{}," folder. After it runs, you'll see a new ",[28,103,104],{},"hueman"," folder under ",[28,107,108],{},"themes",", and inside is the theme template:",[17,111,112],{},[42,113],{"alt":104,"src":114},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FHexo\u002F%E8%A9%A6%E8%91%97%E5%AD%B8%20Hexo%20%E7%B3%BB%E5%88%97\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202020-08-12%2022.10.59.png",[12,116,118],{"id":117},"switching-themes","Switching themes",[17,120,121,122,125],{},"Next, we need to point Hexo's ",[28,123,124],{},"hexo\u002F_config.yml"," at the theme we just cloned.",[17,127,128,129,132,133,135,136,139],{},"Quick reminder: Hexo has its own system ",[28,130,131],{},"_config.yml",", and themes also have their own file with the same name. So when I'm talking about Hexo's config, I write ",[28,134,124],{},", and the theme's is ",[28,137,138],{},"themes\u002F_config.yml",".",[17,141,142,143,145,146,149,150,153,154,156,157,139],{},"Back on track. Open ",[28,144,124],{},", search for ",[28,147,148],{},"Extensions"," or ",[28,151,152],{},"theme",", and put the theme folder name after it. We're using the theme folder ",[28,155,104],{},", so update it to ",[28,158,159],{},"theme: hueman",[17,161,162,163,166,167,170,171,173,174,177,178,181],{},"Now if you run ",[28,164,165],{},"hexo s"," and visit ",[28,168,169],{},"http:\u002F\u002Flocalhost:4000\u002F",", you'll see some errors. That's because after ",[28,172,30],{},", the hueman theme doesn't have a ",[28,175,176],{},"theme\u002F_config.yml"," yet — only a ",[28,179,180],{},"theme\u002F_config.yml.example",". Just run:",[67,183,185],{"className":69,"code":184,"language":71,"meta":72,"style":72},"cp themes\u002Fhueman\u002F_config.yml.example themes\u002Fhueman\u002F_config.yml\n",[28,186,187],{"__ignoreMap":72},[76,188,189],{"class":78,"line":79},[76,190,184],{},[17,192,193,194,196,197,199,200,202],{},"This copies ",[28,195,180],{}," and names the copy ",[28,198,176],{},". Now run ",[28,201,165],{}," again and the page should render correctly:",[17,204,205],{},[42,206],{"alt":104,"src":207},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FHexo\u002F%E8%A9%A6%E8%91%97%E5%AD%B8%20Hexo%20%E7%B3%BB%E5%88%97\u002F1597244970553.jpg",[17,209,210],{},"One last tip — if after switching the theme it doesn't render properly, like this:",[17,212,213],{},[42,214],{"alt":215,"src":216},"Broken render","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FHexo\u002F%E8%A9%A6%E8%91%97%E5%AD%B8%20Hexo%20%E7%B3%BB%E5%88%97\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202020-08-12%2023.10.54.png",[17,218,219,220,223],{},"Try ",[28,221,222],{},"http:\u002F\u002F127.0.0.1:4000\u002F"," instead. If that one renders fine, just clear your browser cookies and the original URL will work.",[17,225,226,227,139],{},"A well-known Hueman user is Casper Wang (free shoutout) — if you're curious you can check out his site ",[89,228,231],{"href":229,"rel":230},"https:\u002F\u002Fwcc723.github.io\u002F",[93],"here",[12,233,235],{"id":234},"hueman-config","Hueman config",[17,237,238,239,241],{},"Open ",[28,240,176],{}," and let's go over what's configurable in this theme.",[17,243,244],{},"Hueman's main config has eight major sections:",[246,247,248,254,259,264,269,274,279,284],"ul",{},[249,250,251],"li",{},[28,252,253],{},"Menus",[249,255,256],{},[28,257,258],{},"Customize",[249,260,261],{},[28,262,263],{},"Widgets",[249,265,266],{},[28,267,268],{},"Search",[249,270,271],{},[28,272,273],{},"Comment",[249,275,276],{},[28,277,278],{},"Share",[249,280,281],{},[28,282,283],{},"Plugins",[249,285,286],{},[28,287,288],{},"Miscellaneous",[17,290,291,292,294,295,297,298,301],{},"The one you'll probably touch most is ",[28,293,253],{},". Say you want to add a page for your portfolio — add it under ",[28,296,253],{}," (remember to use ",[28,299,300],{},"hexo pages working"," to create the page first). The part before the colon becomes the menu name shown on the site:",[67,303,307],{"className":304,"code":305,"language":306,"meta":72,"style":72},"language-yml shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","menu:\n    Home: \u002F\n    # Delete this row if you don't want categories in your header nav bar\n    Categories:\n    About: \u002Fabout\u002Findex.html\n    Working: \u002F\n","yml",[28,308,309,319,332,339,347,358],{"__ignoreMap":72},[76,310,311,315],{"class":78,"line":79},[76,312,314],{"class":313},"sKpQp","menu",[76,316,318],{"class":317},"sMAXC",":\n",[76,320,322,325,328],{"class":78,"line":321},2,[76,323,324],{"class":313},"    Home",[76,326,327],{"class":317},": ",[76,329,331],{"class":330},"sTRMh","\u002F\n",[76,333,335],{"class":78,"line":334},3,[76,336,338],{"class":337},"sQrFR","    # Delete this row if you don't want categories in your header nav bar\n",[76,340,342,345],{"class":78,"line":341},4,[76,343,344],{"class":313},"    Categories",[76,346,318],{"class":317},[76,348,350,353,355],{"class":78,"line":349},5,[76,351,352],{"class":313},"    About",[76,354,327],{"class":317},[76,356,357],{"class":330},"\u002Fabout\u002Findex.html\n",[76,359,361,364,366],{"class":78,"line":360},6,[76,362,363],{"class":313},"    Working",[76,365,327],{"class":317},[76,367,331],{"class":330},[17,369,370,371,374],{},"This will show up on the page, but there's a gotcha — what actually displays is ",[28,372,373],{},"index.working",":",[17,376,377],{},[42,378],{"alt":379,"src":380},"index.Working","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FHexo\u002F%E8%A9%A6%E8%91%97%E5%AD%B8%20Hexo%20%E7%B3%BB%E5%88%97\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202020-08-16%2015.12.51.png",[17,382,383,384,387,388,391,392,395,396,399],{},"That's because Hueman uses language packs for menu names. You need to add the matching entry into the language pack. We're using ",[28,385,386],{},"en",", so open ",[28,389,390],{},"theme\u002Flanguages\u002Fen.yml"," and add ",[28,393,394],{},"working: 'Working'",". The part before the colon matches the menu key (",[28,397,398],{},"Working","); the string after is the display text:",[17,401,402],{},[42,403],{"alt":404,"src":405},"working","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FHexo\u002F%E8%A9%A6%E8%91%97%E5%AD%B8%20Hexo%20%E7%B3%BB%E5%88%97\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202020-08-16%2015.21.15.png",[17,407,408,409,412],{},"If you're using Chinese instead, it's the same approach — just edit ",[28,410,411],{},"theme\u002Flanguages\u002Fzh-TW.yml"," instead.",[17,414,415],{},"Hueman's feature set is on the lean side but covers most needs, so I'll skip the detailed walkthrough — pull it down and play around with it yourself.",[17,417,418],{},"See you in the next theme post.",[420,421,422],"style",{},"html .default .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html pre.shiki code .sKpQp, html code.shiki .sKpQp{--shiki-default:#72F088}html pre.shiki code .sMAXC, html code.shiki .sMAXC{--shiki-default:#F0F3F6}html pre.shiki code .sTRMh, html code.shiki .sTRMh{--shiki-default:#ADDCFF}html pre.shiki code .sQrFR, html code.shiki .sQrFR{--shiki-default:#BDC4CC}",{"title":72,"searchDepth":321,"depth":321,"links":424},[425,426,427,428],{"id":14,"depth":321,"text":15},{"id":22,"depth":321,"text":23},{"id":117,"depth":321,"text":118},{"id":234,"depth":321,"text":235},"Hexo","2020-09-27 00:00:01","md",{},true,"\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002Flearn-hexo-14-hueman-theme","3",{"title":6,"description":19},false,"en\u002FHexo\u002Flearn-hexo-14-hueman-theme",[429,440,441,442],"Learning Hexo from Scratch","iThome Ironman 2020","Hueman",null,"\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2020\u002F09\u002F27\u002Flearn-hexo-14-hueman-theme\u002F","PfYBblNPHQNl-SgC5-vryl2lRe6XkweW8oX-PlPEvZ4",{"newer":447,"older":451},{"url":448,"title":449,"date":450},"\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2020\u002F09\u002F28\u002Flearn-hexo-15-vexo-theme\u002F","(15) Learning Hexo from Scratch - Themes: Vexo","2020-09-28 00:00:01",{"url":452,"title":453,"date":454},"\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2020\u002F09\u002F26\u002Flearn-hexo-13-picking-a-theme\u002F","(13) Learning Hexo from Scratch - Themes: How to Pick a Hexo Theme","2020-09-26 08:26:35",[456,461,465],{"url":457,"title":458,"date":459,"readingMinutes":460},"\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2022\u002F10\u002F30\u002Ffix-hexo-updated-date-on-ci-deploy\u002F","Fix: All Posts Show Updated Date After Hexo Upgrade or CI Deploy","2022-10-30 11:52:35","2",{"url":462,"title":463,"date":464,"readingMinutes":435},"\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2020\u002F11\u002F01\u002Flearn-hexo-33-updating-next-theme\u002F","(33) Learning Hexo from Scratch - Extras: Updating the NexT Theme","2020-11-01 13:21:00",{"url":466,"title":467,"date":468,"readingMinutes":460},"\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2020\u002F10\u002F31\u002Flearn-hexo-32-updating-hexo\u002F","(32) Learning Hexo from Scratch - Extras: Updating Hexo","2020-10-31 14:01:51",1784010275213]